{"slug": "amulet", "root": "amulet", "category": "item", "gloss": "a worn protective charm", "definition": "An amulet is a worn object of protection — a charm that wards off harm passively, by being carried. It contrasts with the *talisman*, which is actively charged to *do* something.", "history": "Latin *amuletum*, 'a charm,' of uncertain origin — perhaps from *amoliri*, 'to avert, to carry trouble away.' The amulet is the oldest wearable technology: Egyptian scarabs, Roman *bullae*, medieval saints' medals all do the same job. Magic uses 'Amulet' for protective and mana artifacts.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Etymonline, s.v. amulet", "where": "Etymology reference"}, {"label": "Geraldine Pinch, Magic in Ancient Egypt", "where": "Reference"}], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"origin": "Latin amuletum ‘a charm’; perhaps from amoliri ‘to avert, remove’", "first": "1600s", "note": "Where a talisman is actively charged, an amulet passively wards — its very name may mean ‘the thing that carries trouble away.’", "hook": "The oldest wearable technology.", "lang": "Latin"}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 5, "oracle_total": 2, "in_flavor_cards": 5, "in_oracle_cards": 2, "name_match_count": 18, "by_variant": {"amulet": 4, "amulets": 3}, "first_year": 1994, "colors": {"U": 1, "C": 14, "G": 4, "W": 2, "B": 1, "R": 1}, "by_year": {"1994": 1, "1995": 1, "1996": 1, "2007": 1, "2008": 1, "2010": 1, "2011": 2, "2014": 2, "2017": 1, "2018": 1, "2020": 1, "2021": 1, "2022": 1, "2023": 1, "2024": 2, "2025": 2, "2026": 1}}, "cards": [{"id": "0edf0988-9ed8-4fe6-aa47-4921870f05a8", "name": "Forethought Amulet", "set": "LEG", "set_name": "Legends", "released": "1994-06-01", "type_line": "Artifact", "rarity": "rare", "colors": [], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/